The paper proposes a method for imputing missing events in continuous time event streams using a trainable family of proposal distributions based on bidirectional continuous-time LSTM. The method involves sequential importance sampling and is evaluated on synthetic and real domains using a neural Hawkes process. This work involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and signal processing, which are all covered by the above sub-categories.
